1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives upon the death of Sharon K.
3 Fontenot.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on March 10,
6 2026, of Sharon K. Fontenot; and
7 WHEREAS, Sharon K. Fontenot was born on December 22, 1944, in Eunice,
8 Louisiana, to Kit and Joyce Fontenot; and
9 WHEREAS, Ms. Fontenot was an incredibly civic-minded woman who served as a
10 Eunice city councilwoman and as president of the Eunice Chamber of Commerce; and
11 WHEREAS, Ms. Fontenot passionately supported Right to Life for fifty-three years
12 and received recognition for her dedicated service at the Bishop's Pro-Life Rose Dinner; and
13 WHEREAS, Ms. Fontenot served as the owner of Coastal Culvert prior to her
14 retirement; outside of her professional and civic duties, she enjoyed traveling, attending
15 daily mass, and watching LSU baseball games; her greatest love was spending time with her
16 family and friends; and
17 WHEREAS, Sharon K. Fontenot is survived by her son, Tommy Fontenot, Jr.
18 (Gwen); daughters, Angelle Manuel (Hayward) and Suzanne Mayer (Vern Johnson);
19 brothers, Gary Fontenot (Paula) and Kevin Fontenot (Pat); sister, Doris Brown (Bobby);
20 twelve grandchildren; twenty-two great-grandchildren; and a host of extended relatives and
